      "title": "Implementation Roadmap: Phases 1-5",
      "content": "Phase 1 (MVP): Core language specification, lexer/parser, basic compiler to LLVM IR, minimal syntax mode. Phase 2 (Neurodivergent): Natural language mode implementation, accessibility features, ADHD/dyslexia support, testing with neurodivergent developers. Phase 3 (AI): GPT integration, Claude compatibility, Mistral support, dynamic prompt generation, context preservation. Phase 4 (Multi-Backend): Quantum backend (Cirq), classical GPU support, neuromorphic compilation paths, DNA computing exploration. Phase 5 (Living Research): AI research agent deployment, knowledge graph implementation, automated documentation, community contribution pipeline. Timeline: Phase 1-2: 6 months (MVP + neurodivergent polish), Phase 3: 3 months (AI integration), Phase 4: 6-12 months (experimental backends), Phase 5: Ongoing (living evolution).",
      "url": null,
      "tags": ["roadmap", "implementation", "phases", "timeline", "milestones"]
    },
    {
      "title": "Open Source Community Strategy",
      "content": "HyperCode is built as open-source from day one with professional community structures: (1) Contributor Guidelines—clear COC, contribution process, code standards; (2) Maintainer Program—onboarding process for long-term contributors; (3) Mentorship System—pairing new contributors with experienced maintainers; (4) Issue Triage—organized, labeled issues with clear complexity levels; (5) Documentation First—prioritize docs as entry point for new contributors; (6) Community Events—monthly dev calls, async discussions, RFCs for major features; (7) Inclusive Leadership—active outreach to underrepresented groups in tech, especially neurodivergent developers; (8) Sustainability—plan for long-term funding, grants, potential corporate sponsorship without compromising values.",
      "url": null,
